1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 {Controlling the central e5-square and preparing Nf6!} 3. d4
{Going for the Open Sicilian.} cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 {Developing the knight, made
possible by our pawn on d6.} 5. Nc3 a6 {This move defines the Najdorf. Now we
want to push e5 and Bb5+ is no longer an issue.} 6. g3 {This is not the most
common system, but it is definitely there and it occurs regularly across all
levels. White wants to fianchetto his bishop, secure his king and play a long
positional game. We don't mind that either.} e5 {The Scheveningen setup with 6.
..e6 , but also the Dragon style 6...g6 are both very much possible here. For
consistency's sake, whenever 6...e5 is good, I recommend it, so let's go with
that here too!} 7. Nf3 {Is a rare move, but there is a romantic, yet rather
unrealistic idea behind it, to manoeuvre the knight to d5 via h4-g2-e3.} Be7 8.
Nh4 O-O {The trick is not to fear 9. Nf5 and not waste a tempo on 8...g6 ,
after which 9.Ng2! would be a lot more justified.} 9. Bg2 {Admission of a
failed bluff.} Bg4 {Also possible is 9...g6!? which is more often played, but
I like this idea here, confusing White's plans.} 10. Bf3 {Other moves aren't
ideal either, again 10.Qd3 is met with 10...Nbd7 and Nc5.} Be6 {The bishop is
now left slightly awkward on f3 instead of g2. Nc6-Nd4 is now a theme.} 11. O-O
b5 {This pawn push works out well here.} 12. Nf5 b4 {Black has plenty of
options, but this unusual idea of forcing the matters so early on gives us a
great position.} 13. Nxe7+ Qxe7 14. Nd5 Nxd5 15. exd5 Bh3 16. Re1 Nd7 {We have
very clear play on the kingside. The only issue is that our b4 pawn is a
target and it is very instructive how we deal with it here.} 17. a3 b3 {A very
beautiful positional pawn sacrifice. We don't want to lose any time or open
White's a1 rook. The pawn deficit will not play much role, as most of the game
will be focused now on the kingside and the center.} 18. cxb3 f5 {White's pawn
majority is far less potent and relevant than Black's here. Our ideas are
pushing f4 to open the f-file or activate the knight with e4 and Ne5.} *

